===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|屵|t1=cliff|干|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p}} – the edge of the land. Its proto-form was {{zh-l|*屵}}.

===Etymology===
Possibly derived from a stem {{m|och||*ŋaʔ|to oppose; to resist}} + general noun suffix {{m|och||*-n}}; related to {{och-l|厂|cliff}}, {{och-l|滸|riverbank}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

